-- Bauba Platinum, Freeworld Coatings: South African Stock Market Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2011-02-04T05:33:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-03/bauba-platinum-freeworld-coatings-south-african-stock-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  South Africa .
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index climbed
307.23, or 1 percent, to 32,794.84 at the 5 p.m. close in
Johannesburg.    Bauba Platinum Ltd . (BAU SJ): Today is the last day of the
company’s “reinstatement agreement” negotiations with vendors
of platinum assets. Bauba rose 2.3 percent to 2.25 rand.    Freeworld Coatings Ltd . (FWD SJ): Kansai Paint Co. Ltd.
said it is now in control of 69 percent of the South African
coating company’s shares and that its offer for Freeworld has
become “unconditional as to acceptances.” Freeworld rose 0.4
percent to 11.44 rand.  Standard Bank Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): Africa’s largest lender
may sell its stake in  Russia ’s Troika Dialog for $360 million,
Johannesburg-based  Business Day  newspaper reported, citing a
report from Renaissance Capital and Russian media reports. The
stock rose 1 rand, or 0.9 percent, to 107.25 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following South
African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUK US) fell 0.4 percent to $26.22.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) added 2.7 percent to $45.41. BHP
Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 0.9 percent to $81.82. DRDGold Ltd.
(DROOY US) gained 0.4 percent to $4.61. Gold Fields Ltd. (GFI
US) advanced 1.1 percent to $16.30. Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HMY
US) gained 1.7 percent to $10.91. Impala Platinum Holdings
(IMPUY US) climbed 0.1 percent to $29.35. Sappi Ltd. (SPP US)
lost 2.8 percent to $5.24. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) rose 0.9 percent
to $49.56.  To contact the reporter on this story:
